The paper discusses the impact of the arXiv e-print repository on citation rates in astronomy and physics. The most relevant arXiv CS sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), as the paper examines the impact of a digital repository on citation behavior. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of citation statistics and information retrieval techniques (such as keyword searching) to analyze the data, which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CY (Computational Geometry), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of data mining and statistical analysis techniques to examine the data, which are relevant to the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
